Here is a working Pine Script for a simple Moving Average Crossover strategy.

This script uses two Simple Moving Averages (SMA): a fast one and a slow one. When the fast SMA crosses above the slow SMA, it generates a "Buy" signal, and when the fast SMA crosses below the slow SMA, it generates a "Sell" signal.

```pinescript
//@version=5
strategy("Simple SMA Crossover Strategy", shorttitle="SMA Cross", overlay=true)

// --- Inputs ---
// Define the lengths for the fast and slow moving averages
fastLength = input.integer(10, title="Fast SMA Length", minval=1)
slowLength = input.integer(30, title="Slow SMA Length", minval=1)

// --- Calculations ---
// Calculate the Simple Moving Averages
fastMA = ta.sma(close, fastLength)
slowMA = ta.sma(close, slowLength)

// --- Crossover Conditions ---
// Determine the crossover conditions
buyCondition = ta.crossover(fastMA, slowMA) // Fast MA crosses above Slow MA
sellCondition = ta.crossunder(fastMA, slowMA) // Fast MA crosses below Slow MA

// --- Strategy Execution ---
// Execute buy and sell orders based on the conditions
if buyCondition
    strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long)

if sellCondition
    strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short)

// Optional: Plotting the MAs for visualization
plot(fastMA, color=color.blue, title="Fast SMA")
plot(slowMA, color=color.orange, title="Slow SMA")
